A **constructor** runs **automatically** right after new. It sets the object up.
java
class Box {
    int value;

    Box() {            // constructor (same name as class, no return type)
        value = 0;     // default setup
    } 
}

public class S4 {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Box b = new Box();            // runs Box() 
        System.out.println(b.value);  // 0
    }
}
